article.headline: Binghamton 78, Alcorn St. 65
article.story: ALBUQUERQUE, N.M. (AP) -- Lazar Trifunovic scored 25 points and Mike Gordon tied the tournament record with 11 assists Friday night in Binghamton's 78-65 win over Alcorn State in the consolation game of the Lobo Invitational. Binghamton (7-5) also got 22 points from Duane James. Trifunovic had 7 rebounds. Alcorn State (1-10) was led by Delvin Thompson's 22 points. Thompson hit 9 of 16 shots. Binghamton led 43-28 at halftime, with Trifunovic scoring 14 points in the opening half. Alcorn State, whose only win this season was against Paul Quinn three weeks ago, hit just 4 of 22 3-point shots and repeatedly fouled the quicker Bearcats, who hit 19 of 29 free throws.
